## Impact

The `sNOTE` and `TreasuryManager` contracts both inherit the `BoringOwnable` contract which is compatible with the `UUPSUpgradeable` standard. This contract allows for a two-step ownership pattern, however, the respective `initialize` functions do not adhere to this pattern. As a result, if there is any mistake in the upgrade process and the `owner` state variable is mistakenly set to the wrong account, all funds will be locked in the `TreasuryManager` contract and `sNOTE` will no longer be able to cover any collateral shortfalls.

