## [L-07] External Calls inside a loop
Calls to external contracts inside a loop are dangerous (especially if the loop index can be user-controlled) because it could lead to DoS if one of the calls reverts or execution runs out of gas. Avoid calls within loops, check that loop index cannot be user-controlled or is bounded.[Reference](https://swcregistry.io/docs/SWC-113)

